Description:
All the Right Ingredients
Impeccably maintained, this elevated three bedroom home has all the right ingredients of an exciting listing including a northerly rear garden and generous allotment of 630m2 (approximately). A carefully constructed owner/builder's home in a great locale, it's making a splash with its market debut and presents a living, dining, large and fully equipped kitchen/meals, sunroom, three double bedrooms and a sparkling bathroom. Bookended by neat gardens it's complete with heating, cooling and a side driveway to a deep automatic garage/workshop. Extra features include roller shutters, a rainwater tank, shed and external powder room. A stroll to transport, parks, Northcote Aquatic Centre and schools, this much loved home presents great possibilities near both High Street and Station Street shops.
Insights: 127 Jenkins Street, Northcote VIC 3070 was last sold in 2020 and 117 other 3 bedroom house in Northcote have recently been sold.

Description:
Inspect today!! $799,000!!
***This property is available for inspection by appointment - Please contact us to arrange a suitable time***
Inner-city living or blue-chip investing, this ground-floor apartment is absolutely perfect either way with its generous design, quality features and unbeatable heart-of-Melbourne convenience. Completely renovated throughout, comprises two double bedrooms (both with built-in robes) and a stylish bathroom complete with floor to ceiling natural stone. Other highlights include a spacious lounge/dining area with timber flooring, leafy outlook and modern kitchen with stainless steel cooking appliances and ample storage cupboards, garden set balcony and its own lock-up garage. The best of Fitzroy and Carlton at your fingertips including Brunswick Street cafes, bars and restaurants, boutique shops and major supermarkets, Carlton Gardens, choice of tram lines, easy access to university/hospital precincts as well as walking distance to Parliament Station and the CBD.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending a Private Appointment, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from our team members, and if requested wait outside until the property is ready for the appointment. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.

Description:
Brilliant Entry into this Exclusive Northcote Neighbourhood
***INSPECTION STRICTLY BY PRIOR REGISTRATION***
A must-see for inner-urban professionals, young families and astute investors alike, this Californian classic presents an immediately enjoyable and versatile lifestyle opportunity along with plenty of scope to further enhance and personalise in the future. Beyond the timeless appeal of its gabled facade, discover a light-filled interior comprising two main bedrooms, as well as a separate lounge/third bedroom and period-inspired bathroom. The home's spacious open-plan living/dining area is accompanied by a contemporary kitchen complete with timber benchtops, soft-close drawers, stainless steel cooking appliances and dishwasher. High ceilings throughout, the home also includes ducted heating and evaporative cooling, ceiling fans (front bedrooms), solid timber floors and laundry with full-width floor-to-ceiling storage cupboards. Outside finds a private back garden with undercover deck/entertaining area, plus a large studio/home office or guest room, handy storage shed and garage/workshop. Zoned to Northcote High School, it's walking distance to Westgarth Primary School, Santa Maria College, Dennis Station and Northcote Station, All Nations Park, as well as Northcote Plaza, High Street cafes and trams.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.
Insights: 24 Sharp Street, Northcote VIC 3070 was last sold in 2020 and 117 other 3 bedroom house in Northcote have recently been sold.

Description:
Parkland Classic in Coveted Sumner Estate
Expressions of Interest Closing Tuesday 12th May at 3pm
Engulfed in parkland with enchanting street aesthetics, this period inspired five bedroom plus study, two bathroom home on 585m2 (approx.) is full of opportunities for family living. Exposed timber beams create a soaring cathedral ceiling that blankets an equipped kitchen with stainless steel appliances and breakfast bar, while two sunlit living spaces open to an all seasons alfresco and impressive deep garden. Generously sized bedrooms with BIRs are split between the ground and top floor; both levels are serviced by a central bathroom, one of which is newly modernised. Featuring hardwood floors, heating/cooling, loads of storage, lockup carport and OSP. Ideally zoned to Northcote High, moments from Merri Park, Merri Creek trails, High Street restaurants/bars, Nicholson Street trams and CBD.

Description:
Peaceful Westgarth Energy Efficient Delight
A double-fronted delight of energy-efficient, contemporary living in a peaceful Westgarth pocket close to beautiful Yarra River parkland. This secluded 3 bedroom residence with a modernist feel reveals relaxed, flowing interior space capturing natural north light. Established native garden, large entertaining deck via stackable sliding doors and child and pet-friendly open spaces embrace this warm and inviting family home. Features include high-rebate solar electricity, rainwater tanks, irrigated vegetable garden and fruit trees, air-conditioning and efficient heating with Nøbo electric plus cozy Nectre wood heater. Located just a short stroll to schools (zoned for Westgarth Primary and Northcote High School), shopping, cafes and train stations and a 20 minute cycle to the CBD. Offering bright living room, open-plan dining and kitchen with concrete bench tops and stainless-steel appliances, double glazed bedrooms, family bathroom, laundry, study nook, Baltic pine flooring, attic storage, spacious workshop and off-street parking for two vehicles with carport.
Insights: 9 Henderson Street, Northcote VIC 3070 was last sold in 2020 and 117 other 3 bedroom house in Northcote have recently been sold.

Description:
Designer living with an architectural edge!
*Please contact us to arrange a Private Inspection*
The latest offering from award winning Taouk Architects delivers a new level of luxury combining design finesse and beauty, in harmony with contemporary form and function.
Currently under construction, Townhouse 2 consists of 2 bedrooms, 2.5 bathrooms & study/retreat. Meticulously crafted, unsurpassed in elegance and bold design, this home showcases progressive living promoting an effortless indoor-outdoor lifestyle with north facing courtyard.
Detailed to demanding specifications, showcasing modern finishes and richly textured materials, inspiring living space flows on the ground floor, featuring state of the art European kitchen, walk in laundry, bespoke bathrooms and seamless open plan living/dining expanding outdoors onto fully landscaped gardens. Exclusive first-class appointments include plush fitted bedrooms, open study room/retreat, high ceilings throughout, air conditioning and heating, secure parking with remote garage & storage.
A privileged lifestyle location, close to Johnson Park, Studley Parklands, Victoria Road shops, High Street Northcote shopping precinct, within Westgarth Primary School zone, Dennis Train Station, Bus 250 to city and Latrobe University, and just 8km from Melbourne's CBD.
Private Sale: $790,000 - $830,000
- Stamp Duty Savings Available.
To arrange an inspection, contact Peter Bozinoski on 0413 136 486.

Description:
Versatile space, modern quality & super-central position
An excellent design of ideal proportions ensures this stylishly updated 2-level residence will suit a range of lifestyle scenarios in a superbly central inner-city location. From low-upkeep family living in the Northcote High and Merri Creek Primary schools' zones to spacious downsizing or a brilliantly situated start, this modern 3 bedroom and study home in a compact landscaped setting has the size, the quality and the credentials to be your perfect match. Immediately surrounded by the area's much-loved cafes, shops (new Coles East Brunswick), schools (Deutsche Schule), trams (Nos. 96 & 11), train station, parks and trails, the position is quiet and 'walk everywhere' convenient while the flexible interior and easy-care garden are secure, private and filled with light. Enhanced by heating/cooling, alarm and beautiful hardwood floors, this impeccably presented home includes lounge room, living room, dining area, bifold doors to entertainment terrace, stunning kitchen (AEG/ASKO appliances, stone benchtops, Blum hardware), bright bathroom (separate shower and bath), powder room, laundry facilities, built-in robes and undercover car space.

Description:
Family Luxury, Perfectly Zoned! (We are Open for Private Inspections - Call Us Now)
Zed Real Estate is cooperating and responding to the Governments restrictions to the Real Estate market in relation to the Covid-19 outbreak by complying with the governments decision to cancel all public open for inspections and auctions and only conducting private viewings for properties.
Our team will follow the advised social distancing regulation put in place of 1.5 meters and will have hand gloves and sanitizing products for use for both ourselves and our clients. We would like to thank you for your understanding during this unprecedented times.
Cutting edge design, impressive proportions and an innovative layout unite in this outstanding family residence built by Glenvill homes. Promising unparalleled luxury and craftsmanship, the sophisticated floor plan features multiple living areas and anchored in the centre of the ground floor of the home is a stunning kitchen equipped with the finest stainless steel appliances, ample bench and cupboard space and plenty of room to entertain your guests.
With a regal sense of grandeur, the stunning ground floor embraces multiple living zones, (formal and informal) offering suitability and comfortability whatever the occasion may be. This home has been crafted to the finest standards and provides you with the perfect opportunity to host a party or spend quality daily family life. Ultimate privacy with all bedrooms situated on the upper level including bathrooms fitted with baths and double vanities. Offering terrific flexibility, this home has been designed to perfection.
Exceptionally appointed with CCTV, ducted heating, evaporative cooling, powder room, remote control garage, solar electricity, Tesla power wall, smart home automation, underground water tank, alarm system and much more. Superbly positioned near popular primary and secondary schools, This blue-chip location allows you the luxury of being able to walk to shops, cafes, restaurants and even close to walking/bike trails, there are many factors that came into account when labelling this suburb the 'most livable suburb' this home is ready to enhance your lifestyle.

Description:
EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST - CLOSING 6TH MAY AT 5.30PM
***This property is available for inspection by appointment - Please contact us to arrange a suitable time****
Set on one of the area's larger allotments (496sqm approx.) , this substantial residence provides a unique family lifestyle opportunity with its exceptionally spacious floorplan, immaculate presentation and terrific scope for future modernisation. Solid as a rock, the home's spotless interior comprises five bedrooms (four with built-in robes), together with a private master ensuite and two additional bathrooms (one on each level). Adding to its family credentials is a spacious rumpus area and light-filled lounge (both upstairs) along with expansive open-plan living and dining areas complemented by a timber-cabinet kitchen with dishwasher, gas cooktop and new wall oven. High ceilings throughout, the home also includes heating and cooling, security shutters, family-sized laundry, under-stair storeroom, front and rear balconies, plus a large north-facing backyard complete with workshop and garage via extra-wide ROW. All this in an exclusive Fitzroy North neighbourhood walking distance to Nicholson Street and St Georges Road trams, cafes and shops, Merri Creek parkland, Capital City Trail and popular schools (zoned to both Merri Creek PS and Northcote HS).
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending a Private Appointment, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from our team members, and if requested wait outside until the property is ready for the appointment. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.

Smart Milieu designer apartment in Collingwood's vibrant heart
***This property is available for inspection by appointment - Please contact us to arrange a suitable time***
Defined by sweeping northerly district views, this smart designer apartment captures the essence of relaxed contemporary living on Level 7 of 'Peel by Milieu'. It occupies an enviable inner city address on the corner of Wellington Street, above the award-winning Congress restaurant, strolling distance to Peel Street cafes, cosmopolitan Smith Street and tram options. A fusion of modern style and bespoke industrial flair by DKO Architects, it showcases a large light filled living and dining area that opens seamlessly onto a covered entertaining balcony enjoying the expansive views. There is also a stunning integrated kitchen with premium Smeg gas appliances, bright double bedroom with built-ins, sleek bathroom and study nook. It features a European laundry, ducted a/c, exposed concrete ceilings, Oak floors, elegant neutral tones plus a basement car space and storage cage. In addition, the plush building provides video intercom, lift access and bike storage.

Description:
Outstanding designer living with own street frontage
Directly fronting Robert Street, the stunning designer façade of this beautiful light-filled townhouse reflects its universal commitment to quality, style and sophisticated space. An absolute standout from award-winning architects' Hayball; this 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom residence merges next-level perfection with as-new presentation highlighting aesthetically deft design elements throughout a brilliantly conceived layout. The location bound by warehouse conversions and creative hubs is sensational offering city-edge convenience near Smith & Gertrude Streets' cafes and shops, trams, East Melbourne hospitals/clinics and Fitzroy Gardens. Including double-glazed windows and doors, split-system heating/cooling, video intercom, LED lighting and oak floors, the north-facing living and dining with feature panelled wall opens to a sun-drenched covered terrace before extending to an excellent kitchen showcasing Ariston/Ilve stainless-steel appliances, sleek stone benchtops and soft-close storage. The 2 bedrooms include built-in robes with the main offering study nook, ensuite and a balcony, while there's also a chic bathroom, laundry and basement car space on title. This immaculate townhouse offered with a host of lifestyle bonuses flaunts its independent standing with class, confidence and contemporary brilliance.

Description:
Elevated Riverside Potential
Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.
Occupying an expansive high-side allotment (781sqm) with wonderfully wide frontage, this mid-century residence provides a family lifestyle of immediate quality and versatility along with exceptional options to rebuild or redevelop (STCA) in one of Alphington's premier streetscapes. Flawlessly presented from start to finish, the home's current floorplan comprises three bedrooms (large master), spotless central bathroom and separate (second) WC. The light-filled lounge is adjoined by a formal dining room which leads through to the contemporary-style kitchen/meals area complete with stainless steel cooking appliances and dishwasher. Other highlights include ducted heating and evaporative cooling, solid hardwood floors, new carpets, security shutters and a full-size internal laundry. Step outside to discover an expansive backyard with undercover patio, large lawn area and working market garden, plus a 3000L watertank, workshop and oversized single garage via side driveway. Moments from Alphington Grammar School and Alphington Primary School, it's also walking distance to Latrobe Golf Club, the open spaces of Alphington Park and endless Yarra trails, close to local cafes and shops, Heidelberg Road buses, Alphington Station and easy freeway access.

If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. Description:
Stunning Single bedroom at the Unique 'Oxley' Apartments
Uniquely designed by award winning architects Elenberg Fraser, the perfectly positioned Oxley Apartments' complex offers the perfect blend of convenience & style. Located in the heart of Collingwood's Foy Heritage precinct, the lush exterior landscapes provide residents with a secure & stunning sanctuary to call home.
This fantastic single bedroom is both modern & unique, offering streamlined contemporary layout maximizing natural light throughout.
The open-plan living & dining area features floor to ceiling windows that open unto a spacious & versatile wintergarden offering extra efficiency in being a wind, noise and weather proof outdoor space throughout all the seasons.
The stylish & convenient kitchen features stone benches, stainless steel appliances and glass splashback. Comprising a generous and well-lit bedroom featuring large built in wardrobe and ample natural light, as well as an immaculately presented bathroom with floor to ceiling tiles & quality fittings. Other features include double-glazed windows, block out roller blinds, split-system with heating and cooling unit, rooftop garden terrace, outdoor BBQ area & plunge-pool.
Conveniently located in close proximity to everything Smith Streets bars & cafes, renowned restaurants, cosmopolitan shopping precincts, The East-Melbourne hospital precinct, Collingwood train station & trams, Fitzroy Gardens & the CBD. This apartment is a perfect opportunity for astute investors or first home buyers.

Description:
"The Old Broom Factory"
***This property is available for inspection by appointment - Please contact us to arrange a suitable time***
A charismatic 3BR warehouse conversion with all the quirks and perks synomonous with this style of property, its impressive proportions, unique features list and private rooftop terrace provide a delightful surprise outside of the norm. Offering clever segmentation and independent spaces, a vast living/dining area greets you (Private portico entrance) off the street with towering ceilings, timber floors, striking lightshaft and expansive modern kitchen with breakfast bar. A cosy log wood heater and exposed brickwork harken back to its warehouse roots.
Level one has two bedrooms and a dedicated central study/home office area, serviced by a family bathroom and excellent storage. Level three allows the flexibility of a third bedroom, or much sought after studio space or second living zone. This top-floor retreat with kitchenette, private ensuite & terrific storage could be used a myriad of ways, its usability further enhanced with its access to the rooftop terrace with sweeping views to the North, West and Southern horizon. Along with the added ambiance of exposed brickwork and original iron beams, the home also includes additional panel heaters, solid hardwood floors, guest powder room on ground level (third WC), discreet laundry facilities plus a single car garage (accessed via Park Street).
In the heart of the bustling St Georges Road village precinct, this wonderful area is adored by locals and offers the magnificent Fitzroy North Library, much loved eateries, bakery's and eclectic retail outlets, as well as the much loved Piedmonte's supermarket. Fitzroy North Primary School/Fitzroy High School are close by, as are the Capital City & Merri Creek Trails, whilst the lush spaces of the Edinburgh Gardens is just a leisurely stroll around the corner. A central location such as this will provide many years of happy living as you enjoy the unique attributes of this wonderful postcode.Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.

Description:
Outstanding Edinburgh Gardens, dual frontage Victorian
A beautiful Hawthorn brick façade and secluded courtyard garden with rear street frontage bookend the classically comfortable, 2-level interior of this 4 bedroom park-view residence with its perfectly preserved heritage detail and enticing potential. The position is Fitzroy North elite as one of an exclusive few double-storey homes fringing the Edinburgh Gardens where within a short stroll are some of Melbourne's best cafes, restaurants, shops and boutiques plus city-bound trams and schools. This utterly unique opportunity offers arched hallway, study with city views, huge main bedroom with balcony, elegant living room, dining room, modernised kitchen, bathroom, laundry, open fireplaces, ceiling roses and Japanned floorboards.

Description:
-UNDER OFFER-
***This property is available for inspection by appointment - Please contact us to arrange a suitable time***
Enviably positioned in one of Melbourne's most exclusive city-fringe neighbourhoods, this freestanding residence displays all the allure of its Victorian origins, whilst proving a rare and rewarding opportunity to transform into a modern-day masterpiece on land of 6.58m x 36.5m(STCA). Beyond the quintessentially captivating Hawthorn-brick facade, discover a wide side hallway with towering ceilings accessing two genuinely large bedrooms, plus a neat bathroom and full-size laundry/separate WC. Add to this a light-filled central lounge which leads through to the dining room and functional kitchen. Other highlights of this heritage home include gas heating, NBN connection, new carpets throughout, ornate plasterwork and original high skirting boards. Step outside to find a sizeable north-facing backyard complete with lawn area, handy storage shed and direct access to the rear ROW. A short stroll to Queens Parade's cool cafes and boutique shops, choice of tram lines and both Rushall and Clifton Hill stations, it's also close to schools (Fitzroy HS and Fitzroy North PS), Merri Creek trails and the open spaces of Edinburgh Gardens. Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

A super-chic sanctuary at the heart of Fitzroy's best
Delivering incredible space and stunning style in the iconic 'George Corner' complex, this 2-bedroom apartment offers effervescent, city-fringe living at its best! Located between Smith and Brunswick Streets, enjoy the buzz of cafes, restaurants, bars, and shopping surrounding, and an easy tram ride to the CBD. With sunlight beaming over Oak floors, a huge open plan layout entertains in chic style, enriched by views to the Dandenongs from a wide terrace. A concealed study aids home-based work, while a stunning Miele kitchen makes ease of catering including an integrated fridge. With 2 bright and airy robed bedrooms, including a city-view balcony to the main, and a spacious, vogue bathroom, the home is finished with ducted heat/cool, secure entry, carpark and storage cage, and communal bike storage.
